choices.text:
that I'm so disillusioned with the world, filled with rage and unhappiness, and sometimes... Okay, you've already heard enough. Now you must pity me because sometimes I just want to burn everything I have created down just to crush my complacency and to send a "Piss off!" note to the world and my parents—a goddamned piece of shit, hurtful note to mock the defeats of my life. I think about the decay of my "society"... I think about the wars... I think about the racism and the selfishness of the world... Just to think adding more cynicism, pessimism to this undeniable ugly reality—that would just make it worst.

How to fucking fight back? How can I fucking fight back?

Sure, I could be a fucking revolutionary, a revolutionary against the society of war, racism, the fuckers who watch the suffering of others happen out of their cup of dirtiness... Sure, I could be an anarchist... Or a communist... But wait a minute... Isn't this what really changes our world? Is this really how the world works? Or am I just a selfish asshole? Yes, I am alone, but I could make someone feel good, I could bring them happiness but am I allowed to? Damn it, am I allowed to? Am I selfish enough? Did I pretend enough to conform to the norm? This defeats me... I can't trust my emotions. Looks to me like I've grown into a corporate slave
